devdoc.author: Fernando Malaspina
devdoc.details: Auction rules: - Bids must be at least 5% higher than the current highest bid. - The base price for the auction is 1 ether. - Auction duration is initially set to 1 hour. - The auction is extended by 10 minutes with every valid new bid made in the last 10 minutes.   This allows other bidders enough time to respond.

params.lastBidder: Address of the bidder who triggered the extension.

params.winnerBid: Value of the winning bid in wei.

params.amount: Amount of the bid in wei.
params.bidder: Address of the wallet that placed the bid.

bid().details: Reverts if bid is not at least 5% higher or if sender is current highest bidder.

returns._0: A list of BidRecord structs containing each bidder's data.
Struct Bid containing the highest bidder and bid amount.

withdrawBalance().details: Function to withdraw balance remaining in the contract

devdoc.title: Public auction for generic assets
